    "name": "Death Knight",
    "epitet": "The Reaper",
    "display": "Death Knight: The Reaper",
    "description": "The Flame Emperor's subordinate, a knight who desires only to fight the strong. Given his name due to his scythe and dark steed. Appears in Fire Emblem: Three Houses.",
    "artist": "Yamao (やまお)　/ INTELLIGENT SYSTEMS",
    "voiceActorEN": "???",
    "voiceActorJP": "？？？",
    "lowestRarity": 3,
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "I have no name. But when people whisper stories of my ghastly deeds, they call me the Death Knight.",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "You look capable of giving me a decent challenge, and yet I cannot fight you. How maddening.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I slough off the past as a snake does his skin. I slink constantly forward, to my next prey. That is all I need.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Soldiers, like weapons, turn dull from disuse. Only by going to battle and shedding blood can one stay sharp.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Some of these so-called \"Heroes\" are clearly weaklings. You would do well to let me cull the herd.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "My blade has been sharpened...and it craves flesh.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Your friend sent me here to impart a message. While I'm here, why don't you let me kill one of your Heroes?",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "I live.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Who will dare face me now?",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Failure is unacceptable.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Did you expect me to be grateful?",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "I have a talent for murder that demands expression. How dare you constrict me? Know that my truest, deepest wish is to engage you in a mortal duel...and, in that duel, to die by your hand. You are capable of ending my life, are you not? I eagerly await that day. Meanwhile, I will sharpen my scythe and slay any weakling foolish enough to cross me.",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
